==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Provokement
<hw>Pro*voke"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act that
which, provokes; one who excites anger or other passion, or incites to
action; <as>as, a <ex>provoker</ex> of sedition</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Drink, sir, is a great <qex>provoker</qex> of three things.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Provoking</ent>⟦br⟧
